=Luoyang qielan ji 洛陽伽藍記=
by 樣衒之, written 547-550

==Literature==
===Translations===
* Yi-t'ung Wang: A Record of Buddhist Monasteries in Lo-yang. Princeton, 1984
* William J. Jenner: Memories of Loyang : Yang Hsüan-chih and the lost capital (493 - 534). Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1981
===Articles===
* Whalen Lai: Society and the Sacred in the Secular City: Temple Legens of the Lo-yang chief-lan chi. In Albert E. Dien, State and Society in Early Medieval China. Stanford, 1990